Description: Cloudtools developed the industry's first drag and drop solution that allows you move any virtualized machine from anywhere to anywhere.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Based in Austin Texas, Cloudtools was founded in 2014. The story of Cloudtools actually begins earlier at Virtual Bridges, an established player in the virtualization space and the source company from which Cloudtools spun out. At the time, Virtual Bridges was bringing a new product to market, a cloud orchestration solution for orchestrating workloads in multi-cloud environments. During the development period they ran into the same roadblock that Cloudtools customers encounter every day: the time-consuming and difficult task of moving a virtual machine from one environment to another. Virtual Machine movement has been next to impossible yet it is a problem affecting any administrator who has a need to move to a different virtualization platform. We had an advantage when it came to dealing with this roadblock: our development team was dev-ops focused. We had developers who approached this problem with a deep understanding of the operational aspects of virtualization, and had first-hand experience dealing with real-world virtualization problems such as moving VMs. At this point we decided to solve the movement problem once and for all. This is when we formed Cloudtools and created Shift, the drag and drop solution that lets you move any virtualized machine from anywhere to anywhere. Shift is our first product to market that helps to solve the tough problems faced by cloud and virtualization administrators every day. Whether you need a tool that lets you switch to AWS, switch to Hyper-V, switch to Azure or you are having problems or issues with VMware or just want to move to the cloud, Cloudtools has developed the solution to help you. At Cloudtools, our mission is simple: We make tools that let IT professionals spend a few minutes handling tasks that would otherwise take hours or days.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Internet Services, Software

Description: AbDisc is the Fitness Tracker developed specifically to Reduce Sedentary Time and improve Core Fitness.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: AbDisc Core Fitness Tracker The Headlines scream it; “Their Desks are Killing them”. But 96 Million American workers still sit all day; at work, commuting, watching TV...13 hours a day! Called Sitting Disease by doctors, it increases the risk of dying by 50%; from diabetes, heart disease, cancer. Even if you exercise regularly! AbDisc keeps you active throughout the day, automatically. Worn in the waistband, it senses when you're inactive, and coaches you through 90 second isometric "Crunch Sessions" as you go about your day. Simply sit up straight and engage your core, and AbDisc vibes if you slouch or try to relax. Sessions repeat every 15 minutes when you're inactive, and no one will even notice! AbDisc tracks your steps, distance, and calories like all those wristband trackers, but only AbDisc gives you an easy way to be less sedentary.  AbDisc connects wirelessly to your phone to chart your progress, share with friends, reward your efforts, and keep you motivated!

Description: FlightPartner is a software company that provides an online platform for buying and selling travel trips.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: FlightPartner is an Air Charter Commerce platform that offers detailed aircraft search results with the ability to quote, book and pay for air charter travel in real-time.  In short, we match charter broker demand (travel) with air charter operator supply (aircraft). How are we able to accomplish this on a global basis? FlightPartner aggregates global charter aircraft availability and brings that availability to the marketplace through scheduling systems integration and an easy to use cloud-based customer workflow platform. What makes us different than other solutions? With a team of aviation information technology professionals, we are addressing a fragmented air charter industry with poor conversion to sales. Current expensive solutions have flooded the marketplace with request for quotes (RFQ’s) with little expectation of the quote converting to a sale.  We are vetting the charter request process and bringing the sale to the charter operator.  We are able to accomplish this at a fraction of the cost of the largest marketplace. How much does it cost? Our air charter operators can provide access to their aircraft fleet at no cost.   How do we make money? We charge a small transaction front end fee to the broker when the air charter sale is closed.  Unlike other solutions where you incur a subscription fee whether they bring you sales or not, when you make money, we receive a small transaction fee.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Minneapolis-Saint Paul Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Founded in 1998 as MiSFiTS (the Minnesota Society for the Interest in Science Fiction and Fantasy), they have established a tradition of year-round programs by and for local geeks. From their educational initiative of bringing science into local classrooms, to a movie club, to things as simple as an ice cream social, they have always believed that there are great opportunities for service and fun, even if they have to create them. As 2009 drew to a close, they determined they could and should become more. They believe it is time for a community institution dedicated to serving the local geek community. That means providing a facility for work and events to happen. That means building more programs and events to host in that facility. That means networking with the geeks around us to do all of this in new and exciting ways. What it really means is a community center. The idea is hardly new, but in years of dreaming, nobody has put together something like this before. There are a couple very successful science fiction clubhouses out there, and they helped inspire us to take the idea beyond the next level. Now, they think, the time is right. They are committed to making that happen, and this website will show you their progress as they go forward. The Twin Cities are, by many measures, one of the geekiest places to live in the world. It can be done, and it will be done here. Want in?

Description: ENS publishes late-breaking news of the environment from across the United States and around the world.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Environment News Service is the original daily international wire service of the environment. Established in 1990 by Editor in Chief Sunny Lewis and Managing Editor Jim Crabtree, the company is independently owned and operated under the direction of the founders. With the belief that well-informed people are the best guarantee of democracy, The Environment News Service exist to provide late-breaking news of the environment from across the United States and around the world. With the conviction that ignorance is responsible for degradation of Earth’s ecosystems and knowledge can result in planetary health, ENS management and correspondents strive to provide news that is factual and presented without bias. ENS staffers and correspondents file stories to the central ENS editorial desk. In addition to being journalists, ENS contributors may be experts in other fields such as law, ecology, economics or public health. ENS news reports are indexed by Dow Jones Factiva and ProQuest. Hundreds of websites feature ENS headlines and reports. TV websites from all the major U.S. networks and many independents carry ENS reports. ENS covers issues and events that affect the environment such as: natural disasters, politics, legislation, conferences, demonstrations, legal action, international agreements, sustainable development, climate change, energy, nuclear issues, public health, air quality, drinking water, oceans and marine life, land use, forests, wildlife, hazardous materials, toxics, energy, solid waste and recycling, transportation, environmental economics and the built environment. ENS has been first with many stories over the years and has covered emerging issues long before other news services. As a result, ENS has won four Project Censored awards, given by the California-based media research project for news published ahead of the media curve. Many news sources in the United States and around the world contact their newsroom well in advance of public announcements and work closely with us on breaking developments.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

Through routine inspections and adjustments, chiropractors offer their patients important, non-invasive, preventative healthcare. An vast knowledge of vertebral displacement science is at the heart of such specialist and trained care. When one or more vertebrae in the spine are out of place, compressing spinal nerves and impairing ideal nerve function, this is known as a vertebral dislocation. These misalignments are the main focus of chiropractic and they are located, examined, and corrected. Adjustments are used by chiropractors to assist the nervous system and restore joint function. They assist people in maintaining their health while avoiding needless medication or surgery.

Description: Every person is different. Every family is different. Every home is different.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: Every person is different. Every family is different. Every home is different. And one way or another when it comes to home care, every situation is different. At Home For Me Home Care, we honor those differences. That’s why a thorough in-home client assessment is first completed by a Registered Nurse. The details of that assessment create the foundation for a custom plan designed around the needs and wants of the client and his or her family. The focus of the plan is always to support a client with the services required to maintain his or her dignity and freedom, and to develop a safe environment in the home.Each client is matched with a fully-trained, educated, experienced and insured caregiver most suited to his or her situation. There is no need for a client or family to predetermine the needs of the client, as the assessment will determine what needs are present. A special log-in for each family is created on the Home For Me Home Care website under the “Client Services” tab. This portal allows families, regardless of distance, to stay continuously updated on the status of their loved ones through an easy-to-access online system of feedback from the caregivers. A Registered Nurse oversees each plan on a continuous basis to ensure that clients’ and their families’ needs are met, as well as to ensure that plans are altered accordingly to reflect any new situations or circumstances.

Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Miller's Synthetic Turf and Putting Greens installs synthetic turf systems for individual homeowners, commercial properties, sports fields and government facilities. We're a family artificial grass installation company that's focused on offering the highest quality products from the best artificial turf manufacturers.  Since joining the industry over 10 years ago, owner Jason Miller explains that the rapidly-changing artificial turf market has contributed to the widespread use of poor quality products, and worse, the emergence of companies who cut corners on their installs to drive up profits: “The products we offer, of which some are 100% recyclable, are satisfying specific install requirements, like helping designers and architects gain LEED certification points, helping homeowners address specific drainage requirements or enhance their properties. Whatever your unique needs, we'll help you find the right products for your project.” All Miller’s turf systems are installed with a proper drainage system and are backed by an ten-year warranty. “We’ve installed millions of square feet of artificial turf at homes, businesses, dog kennels, golf courses, children's day care facilities and more, so we know how to do the job right the first time,” Jason says. Customers can visit Miller’s Synthetic Turf at their Rocklin showroom to learn about the practical applications for turf and examine a variety of synthetic grass products being displayed. For an ever faster response, click here for a free design quote or call Miller's Synthetic Turf & Putting Greens now at 844-NEW-TURF. Our service areas include: Sacramento, Rocklin, Pleasanton / Dublin, San Ramon, Concord, Walnut Creek, Livermore, Hayward, Vallejo, Fairfield and other Bay Area locations  Company Philosophy “Satisfying our customers is our first priority. We're always striving to provide the best products available along with high-quality workmanship and installations. Our installation team is comprised of our own employees. We don't subcontract work. We’re certified and trained by Pro Green to ensure the proper installation of our clients’ investment."
